
From https://cafedelites.com/ham-potato-soup/

1/3 C butter
1     onion, finely chopped
1   C carrot, peeled and diced
1/2 C celery, diced
3   C potato, peeled and diced
4     garlic cloves, minced/chopped
1.5 C diced ham
1/3 C flour
2   C chicken broth
3   C milk
1/4 t salt

Melt butter in large stock pot.
Saute onion, carrots, celery (~4 minutes)
Add ham and potatoes, cook ~2 minutes
Add garlic and saute about 30 seconds
Mix in the flour, cook 2 minutes
Stir in the stock and mix, cook 10-12 minutes, stirring
Reduce heat, add milk and cook ~5 minutes
